Scanning


There are two TCP ports open on the target machine: SSH and HTTP. The HTTP application on the higher port 10000 is running MiniServ 1.890 (Webmin httpd). I will start enumeration with this application.

Enumeration

Port 10000: HTTP

The webpage above is displayed for this application. I tried a few different default credentials, such as admin:admin, but I had no luck.


However luckily, the target host is running a vulnerable version of the webmin that allows RCE. Ther versions 1.890-1.920 are affected by this RCE according to EDB. This exploit does not require authentication either.

Exploitation & Flags


I downloaded the exploit from above and ran it against the target machine. The target machine executed the command id, as shown above meaning it is vulnerable to RCE.


Since the exploit lands a session as the root, I obtained the shadow file and obtained the password hash of the user dark.



Using the first exploit, I was unable to gain a reverse shell connection. I found another public exploit that gave me a reverse shell connection and I used that instead.
